title: For Sale:  Pre-Healey ban
postcontent: Stop posting "Pre-Healey ban" rifles. Thats not a thing. It doesn't have to have been registered before 7-20-16 for you to buy, sell or possess. Only FFL's can't sell them to people. If someone moves to Massachusetts with an AR or AK after 7-20-16 they need to register the rifle with the state and they are free to sell it if they want in the state. So your "pre-Healey ban" rifle isn't a pre-ban anything and it isn't worth more than an actual pre-ban (ie. pre 94). So stop asking for more than an Colt SP1 or Norico 56s because it isn't as good and isn't worth what you think it is.
